rComments: Great professor for MAT223 (Linear Algebra), lecture style is good and I found myself encouraged to participate during the class. Lecture speed is good, he doesn't rush through everything, and everyone has a chance to keep up.

Professor Jonathon was a great professor. He would always put up a lecture outline each lecture, and go over a ton of examples as he taught. He would also stop frequently to ask if every1 was keeping up. The tests and exam were based off of lectures & practice problems and he was always willing to go the extra mile to help you out. 110% recommended

Arguably the worst professor I've ever had the displeasure of having during my 3 years at UTM. There hasn't been a lecture without him making a string of mistakes in his lectures, erasing nearly EVERYTHING and then re-writing things in parts, confusing the whole class. Horrid, bland lectures. If you have him, I hope you got YT and google on you.
